The scanf() function reads the sequence of characters until it encounters a whitespace (space, newline, tab etc.).\n
You can use gets() function to read a line of string. And, you can use puts() to display the string.\n
To input two integers separated by a space on a single line, the command is scanf("%d %d", &n, &m), where  and  are the two integers.\n
The sum of numbers on two opposite faces of a dice is 7.

